#Text=Previously named  Caution Cube " because there was a big chance to pinch your fingers with the gears . [ 9 ]

column1: #Text=It was mass-produced by Mèffert 's in 2010 , [ 10 ] but over time it appeared as several copies and shape mods of the same design .
#Text=A bandaged version of the Gear cube , where 4 gears are replaced with 4 standard edges , making the puzzle harder .
#Text=It was mass-produced by Mèffert 's in 2010 , [ 11 ] and was also copied by other companies .
#Text=It was mass-produced by Mèffert 's in 2011 ; [ 12 ] a knock off version also appeared .
#Text=Previously called " Polo cube " in reference to Alex Polonsky , who had the idea . [ 13 ]
#Text=A variant of the gear cube where all faces can perform 90 °rotations , allowing centers to be interchanged with edges , hence the term " mixup " .
#Text=An unknown Chinese company mass-produced this puzzle in 2015 using a 3D printed sample , without the permission of Oskar .
#Text=An agreement was met to please both sides . [ 16 ]
#Text=A mass-produced spherical Gear cube made by Mèffert 's . [ 17 ]
#Text=Previously called " Fadi cube " , it is a corner turning puzzle with two cut depths similar to Okamoto and Greg 's " Lattice Cube " .
#Text=Craters on the balls block and unblock movement on the adjacent balls .
#Text=a 3×3×3 Rubik 's cube that can perform 45 °rotations on the middle layers , allowing centers interchange with edges .
#Text=A 3×3×3 puzzle that when solved , can be opened , revealing a small chamber inside .
#Text=A face turning icosahedron with jumbling movements .
#Text=Was mass-produced by LanLan without Oskar 's permission in 2016 but a deal was archived later . [ 24 ]
#Text=A corner turning puzzle mass produced by Moyu in 2017 . [ 25 ]
